---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import productionLine from '../assets/images/production-line.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="OEM Capping Chuck Compatibility | Zalkin, Krones, AROL, CSI"
    description="Reference index of common capping machine OEMs and platform families used in aftermarket chuck and headset discussions."
    canonical="https://cappingchucks.com/oem-compatibility/"
    ogTitle="OEM Compatibility Index | CappingChucks.com"
    ogDescription="Drop-in aftermarket capping chucks and headsets for Zalkin, Krones, AROL, CSI, and Tedelta capping platforms."
    schemaType="TechArticle"
    breadcrumb="OEM Compatibility"
>
    <header class="pt-20 pb-12 border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
            <p class="font-mono text-[0.7rem] text-teal-700 tracking-wider uppercase mb-2"><a href="/" class="no-underline hover:underline">Home</a> / OEM Compatibility</p>
            <h1 class="mb-4">OEM Compatibility Index</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-light leading-relaxed max-w-xl">Reference index of OEM platform families covered in aftermarket chuck and <a href="/capping-headsets/">capping headset</a> work. Confirm interchangeability against the exact machine model, spindle geometry, and closure format before ordering.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="py-16 border-b border-border">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-6">Platform Cross-Reference</h2>

                <figure class="mb-8 -mx-6 sm:mx-0">
                    <Picture
                        src={productionLine}
                        alt="Glass bottles on a rotary capping turret at a wine bottling facility"
                        class="w-full h-56 sm:h-72 object-cover rounded-lg"
                        widths={[600, 900, 1200]}
                        sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"
                        formats={['avif', 'webp']}
                        quality={80}
                        loading="lazy"
                    />
                    <figcaption class="mt-2 px-6 sm:px-0 font-mono text-[0.68rem] text-ink-faint">Rotary capping turret on a glass bottle line. Photo: Pexels</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <div>
                    <div class="oem-entry">
                        <p><span class="oem-name"><a href="https://www.zalkincapping.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Zalkin</a></span><span class="oem-parent">ProMach</span></p>
                        <p class="oem-desc">Zalkin rotary cappers run on beverage and food lines. For aftermarket fit-up, check the spindle interface, closure-handling geometry, and torque-control method on the installed machine.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="oem-entry">
                        <p><span class="oem-name"><a href="https://www.krones.com/en/products/machines/capper-models-for-a-wide-range-of-applications.php" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Krones AG</a></span><span class="oem-parent">Krones Group</span></p>
                        <p class="oem-desc">Krones capping stations cover most beverage line types. Fit-up depends on the capper configuration, cap-handling geometry, and change-part stack on the actual machine.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="oem-entry">
                        <p><span class="oem-name"><a href="https://www.arol.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">AROL S.p.A.</a></span><span class="oem-parent">AROL</span></p>
                        <p class="oem-desc">AROL machines run tethered, ROPP, and standard formats. Verify spindle connection, closure-contact geometry, and chuck-interface material before ordering aftermarket tooling.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="oem-entry">
                        <p><span class="oem-name"><a href="https://www.csiclosures.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">CSI</a></span><span class="oem-parent">Closure Systems International</span></p>
                        <p class="oem-desc">CSI equipment runs multiple closure formats, including aluminum roll-on. Don't assume fit from the brand name; verify against the installed machine configuration.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="oem-entry">
                        <p><span class="oem-name"><a href="https://us.tedelta.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Tedelta</a></span><span class="oem-parent">Tedelta</span></p>
                        <p class="oem-desc">Tedelta equipment runs on pharmaceutical and cosmetic lines. Check replacement compatibility against the machine serial, spindle arrangement, and validated closure format.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="callout">
                    Brand names are trademarks of their respective owners and are referenced here for cross-identification only. Exact replacement compatibility should be confirmed from machine records, drawings, or sample-part qualification.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-16 pb-20">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-4">Related</h2>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-[0.92rem]">
                    <li><a href="/chuck-types/">Capping Chuck Types</a> -- magnetic, friction, pneumatic, and vacuum classifications</li>
                    <li><a href="/capping-headsets/">Capping Headsets</a> -- headset assemblies and torque delivery mechanisms</li>
                    <li><a href="/troubleshooting/">Troubleshooting & Calibration</a> -- diagnostics for chuck and headset issues</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
